We welcome this announcement warmly.'
Ian Green, president of the Terrence Higgins Trust, said: 'The priority right now should be to ensure that the experiment is presented quickly across the country and that no one with HIV risk is left behind.
Now that the PREP experimental drug has been supplied, we are on the right track to protect more than 10,000 people at risk of HIV.'
Shadow public health minister Sharon Hodgson said: 'We welcome that the PREP experiment has begun, and it has been late with months of delays and then the government's resilience.
